OL,4,CIndia 'has 21 million unwanted girls'
OL,5, The desire among parents in India to
OL,6, have sons instead of daughters has
OL,7, created 21 million "unwanted" girls, a
OL,8, government report estimates.
OL,10,FThe finance ministry report found many
OL,11,Fcouples kept on having children until
OL,12,Fthey had a boy.
OL,14,FAuthors called this a "subtler form" of
OL,15,Fson preference than sex-selective
OL,16,Fabortions but warned it might lead to
OL,17,Ffewer resources for girls.
OL,19,FSon preference was "a matter for Indian
OL,20,Fsociety to reflect upon", they said.
